messages.content: Rikarasu awakens mysteriously not in her bed but at her desk. Quite mysterious. Already a mystery. She has a meeting scheduled with Haruka, but not until some time later. What will she do?

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She stretches out at her seat and takes in her surroundings for a moment.* "Huh-uh? That's funny."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I'm not getting mixed up, surely? I did fall asleep in bed?" *She laughs.* "What a mystery!"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She shuffles around in her pockets and checks that she has still has what she'd expect on her (pen and kazoo).*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: She does.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Weird." *She then pulls out her hands and gets up, grabbing the pocketbook she obviously has on her desk and leaving the office for her bedroom.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: Rikarasu’s bedroom, which, as it turns out, is a separate room from the one in which she has a desk, has absolutely nothing out of the ordinary.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "...Nothing? Maybe I'm pranking myself."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Sleepwalking?" *She thinks to herself for a moment.* "I bet there's something more to this. Why not?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I'm still barely able to deduce anything here while barely knowing the basics." *She exits.* "No blatant signs of damage on the window in there, at least."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Not that that proves much without further scrutiny. I'd presumably be woken up by any loud noises."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She walks back through the office and to the front door, which she opens and examines at the front for any visible signs of forced entry.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: Roll investigation

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: As far as she can tell, there’s no signs of forced entry.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She flips open her pocketbook and jots down a few notes: "unusual arousal in office", dated today, "no obvious signs of damage to bedroom window", "no visible signs of forced entry to front door".*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Quite the tough case, but perhaps I should just take the opportunity for practice. Or perhaps I'm being tested by somebody?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She shrugs.* "There's nobody here to work with now, but at least a mystery is a mystery. If somebody was to go out of their way to move me, it'd be to some ends, no?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "What motive could I imagine for that? To stop me from feeling something placed underneath or inside the bed? A bomb?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "That'd explain everything so far." *She walks back to her bedroom.* "Indeed, just below this mattress, there could be a ticking time bomb, hidden from sight and from dreams in this perfectly ordinary-looking room!"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She bends down and, with a swift motion, shoves the mattress aside.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: There is nothing under the mattress 1984 gif

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She chuckles and pushes it back into place.* "That would've been pretty ridiculous. But the thread of logic's not bad, right?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "What from that? I am acting as my own client, after all." *She jots down "nothing left under mattress".* "Motive... would someone really want to assassinate me? Is there a connection to anything recent?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "That doesn't add up. A bomb in here wouldn't be assassination because I was moved, and anyone would have the full ability to do anything to me while I was asleep. There's no reason somebody would just want to destroy my bedroom, too. So I can't see a good reason anything would've been placed to act on a short-term basis while necessitating the movement."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Them wanting to hide something is still reasonable. Hiding what that I wouldn't inevitably notice sooner-or-later? Do they aim to distract me while somebody's still inside right now?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "It would still be possible that I was moved hours ago and they already left, but if the timing was right, I could easily catch them in the act now. So how about it?" *She semi-excitedly heads around and looks inside each room of the house (bathroom first) for any lurking criminals.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: Rikarasu looks around all four rooms in her home, but there is still not anyone there who is not her.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She laughs.* "This is fun! But... even with its unexpectedness, it can only go so far with nobody else here. I'm just on the stage of investigation, and not with much progression. At that point, I may as well just try for fingerprints."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I'm really just messing around, though. I can't glean much about having woken up in a different room. In a mystery novel, this would be the prelude, a weird event foreshadowing the main course."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: Rikarasu lampshades the part where she spent two hours in her own home staring at nothing. She eschews storytelling convention, and will not be stopped.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Maybe I should call someone over? Haruka should be meeting me sooner or later, but I doubt she'd be interested. Yasuyasu, if he'd even be available? Or... the police? I'd definitely need to lie to convince them to come out, and even then they don't seem like the most willing conduits for discussion, especially depending on who comes out. But it'd be a real showdown!"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She considers her options.* "If Haruka gives me the opportunity to pounce on a mystery, I'd be better not get that caught up in this one for fun. I'll just..."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She enters what is presumably the fourth room and makes some jam-covered toast for breakfast, which she then eats.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: Rikarasu enjoys the toast, regardless of if it's still morning or not.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *After enjoying her food, she gets up to go to the bathroom and brushes her teeth.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: This goes well.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Very cool

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She returns to her office and grabs a suitable book to maintain the right mood, then sits down at her desk and starts to pass the time with reading.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *After successfully passing the time, she puts it down.* "...I need to head out soon."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: She kinda does.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She gets ready to leave, takes her [NECESSARY DETECTIVING SELF-DEFENSE WEAPON], and departs from her house to the meeting place.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: She is interrupted by her neighbor Alicia. "Ah, you seem busy, I just... whenever you're free, could you help me with something? It's a case, I guess."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Of course." *Fainda nods.* "I am concerned with another mystery, but share the case and I shall assist you when I have the time to."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She opens her pocketbook and looks at Alicia expectantly.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Thanks, yeah." She hands you [CURRENCY EQUIVALENT TO TEN US DOLLARS] and rushes away back into her home.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She pockets the money, jots down "pending case from Alicia" and "small payment hastily given" on a new page, and continues on her way.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: That's Haruka, officially represented, waiting outside a cafe. Rikarasu has successfully gauged time and how much of it has passed.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She approaches the beloved character with no heart.* "...Good afternoon."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Not really." She briefly glances at you before looking back into the middle distance. "You're free the rest of the day, I assume?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I am prepared to work without interruption."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Mm." She hands you a piece of paper with an address written on it. "The client's here. Something about stolen goods. You'll get more information there. He paid in advance." She slips you [CURRENCY EQUIVALENT TO 500 US DOLLARS].

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *Instinctively, she recognizes ~64,700 yen from her reasonable currency background and pockets it, holding the paper.* "I see. Thank you."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: Haruka nods, and leaves.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She looks down at the address and checks if she can vaguely identify its physical locus from any memory.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: You've been to this part of town for work before. Not this exact street or anything.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She looks around the area outside the café for one of Japan's famous payphones and/or a vacant taxi.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: there's?? a taxi sure???

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: ((failure to possess any modern technology luckily leads to The Driver(TAP)))

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She approaches the taxi and gets in.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Where will it be, old chum?" The Driver (TAP) asks this.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She reads the address aloud.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Ah, Danny." He mutters half to himself and then drives you there (this is his job (he's The Driver)).

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She starts another page: "stolen goods case", reception dated today, "payment given in advance", the address, and "residence of Danny?". As they arrive, she hands him the fare.* "I would like a receipt, please."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: The Driver painstakingly writes out a receipt, having no means to print one. It's a really great receipt, basically indistinguishable from the genuine mechanically produced article.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She gives him a look of slight amusement and folds and pockets the receipt.* "Thank you." *She then opens the door and leaves the car.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: These things happen. The street is a fairly well off part of the city, nice houses not far from commercial districts. Rikarasu is BY the house

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She knocks at the door.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: After some time, a muscular man with a goatee opens the door. "Ah. Fainda, I presume? It's good to see you. I'm Ryuki Kazuma."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She nods.* "Detective Fainda Shinjitsu. Are you my client?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Yeah. I have a uh... sensitive item missing. Please, come in."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She steps inside.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: Rikarasu.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She takes another step forward just for good measure.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Thanks."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She then looks towards him.* "A sensitive item missing? Please elaborate."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "It is..." He looks around him from side to side before continuing. "...a music box. It's been in my family for some time. I occasionally bring it in my coat pocket as a good luck charm, of sorts. It's not a very 'cool' thing, so I'd like to keep this quiet."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Your sensitivities are of no concern to me. To want to hide the truth out of shame is little different from sin."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Yes... perhaps I've been a fool."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She notes down "stolen item: music box", "family heirloom", "kept in coat pocket as good luck charm"  and turns to the next page. "Ryuki Kazuma", "client", "cares for appearances", "self-conscious", "possibly not upfront".*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She looks up at him again.* "For you to carry such an item in your coat pocket, I presume it would be of the smaller variety. When did you lose it?"

author.name: pichuis

There's people out there who don't like me, but I think they'd all resort to something more extreme if they wanted to screw with me in particular."

Ryuki has a sad look in his eyes. "So, she would elect to..."

messages.content: "He lives there. It's a whole thing with him, don't ask. That was gonna be the whole thing, he stole from me by reaching up from a drain while I was sitting by the curb briefly. He wasn't supposed to just stand around outside my home like a dumbass."

messages.content: *She keeps her weapon fully trained on Souta.* "What do you mean to suggest about Ms. Tanaka? An elaborate deception? Answer me!"

messages.content:
Ryuki. "Yes, I knew the entire time. I thought this was an eccentric ARG thing for a friend of hers, I didn't think she was actually..."

Ryuki tells him to shut it. "I don't think it's my place to talk to you about this. I would suggest having a real conversation with your employer about your work."

messages.content: "Souta doesn't know the whole story, no. I just told him to do what we saw today, minus the part where he's an idiot."

messages.content: "Exactly. His mockery is merely that of a fool who refuses to grasp the truth."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "You, however, know everything. Burrowing further down on the path of treachery leads only to further failure."

messages.content: "And what were you doing with that deer?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: It looks at you with the face it doesn’t have. “It’s dead.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “Oh, but not from me. I scared off what did it.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "What did it?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: “A bear, maybe? I thought… maybe it could come to again after resting here a bit, and we’d have a win-win… thing, but it seems too late for that.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "A bear likely kills to eat. Its victims would be beyond saving."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She repeats her earlier question.* "Where are we?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content:
“I don’t know… what bears do.”
It rotates a full 360 degrees. “We are… in a cave.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “You seem… hostile. Are you… discomforted by my appearance?” It’s flesh(?) distorts, forming an elegant skirt that is still pure white. “Is this better?” Same as before, but a mock white suit and tie. “Or your preferences… lie here?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I do not intend to be hostile, but your appearance goes against reality. Its existence unshakeably implies an illusion."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Can you explain your colouration?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: “I do not have… color.” It (they?) raises their hand to the deer, draining out and removing its pigment. “I eat it. I guess… you don’t.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "How do you?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: “Like that.” Points to white deer. “I just did it.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "By what means did you transfer the colour into your body? How was your hand able to remove it?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: Blanche pauses for a bit. “Have you heard of… photo synthesis? I think it’s like that.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She pauses for a beat.* "I am well-educated. Photosynthesis is a process passively performed by plants which converts sunlight into energy."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Light... is what causes colors, right? So I do that too. With another step."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "...Where is this cave?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "There is... a plain outside. Some trees. Further beyond is farmland. There are... people there. I do not go there anymore."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Why?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I am hit by them. I don't like this."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She thinks.* "Did you attempt to drain their colour?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "One time, to... someone in the plain. She was very loud, and ran. I do not do it to people anymore."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Understood."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She gestures to the illuminated darkness around her.* "Did you consume the colour of this area?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Only in desperation. The darker earthen tones are... unpleasant."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Why do you choose to remain around them? Is the greater outdoors not an option?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She pulls out the PDA and texts.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: It points to the right (your right). "There is... water that way. I cannot swim." Then the left. "I have not found anywhere worth taking shelter in that way." And then points to the direction further in the cave. "Climbing a mountain is... hard."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "What would happen to you if you entered the water for too long? You do not have a visible receptacle to breathe."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I don't know. I do not know what circumstances cause me to die. But becoming soaked in water causes.... my movements to become more and more sluggish."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "And if you fail to eat?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I guess I would stop being able to do things like move and make noises."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She chuckles.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I intend to leave. Extracting more about you is pointless at this stage."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "But I must ask a final question... What country are we in? Farmland does not fit the climate of Antarctica."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Ant? No, we are in... Arctica."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I think."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "There is no country named Arctica."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Oh. I'm sorry."

messages.content: "Attempt to name the surrounding countries. I expect you have some knowledge that can identify it, even if the name you gave for this country itself is inaccurate."

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "You appear to be both disfigured and delusional. This location is likely a psychiatric hospital, where your belief in the ability to consume colour is kept alive by technological illusion."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Is that so?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "It is. I assume you have no proof otherwise?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Not that I know of."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Very well. I shall depart... for now." *She quietly walks to the path to the left.*

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Where?"

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "In Oku's house. Of Oku. He's the one that was killed."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Who was Oku?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "A simple farmer. None of us knew him that well, which is why we can't nail down when he was killed, only when his body was discovered. Nobody bothered to check in on his house for a week. Except for some bigwig from the government, apparently. There's a lot of chatter, I'm trying to figure out the actual witnesses m'self."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I am a detective. If your goal is to solve this murder, I will happily assist in the investigation."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Oh, thank goodness. Someone who vaguely knows what they're doing, or is willing to pretend. Please, for the love of ovan, try to convince these folks of that."

messages.content: "I shall."

messages.content: "What are the names of this town and the country it resides in? I am a foreigner, in a sense."

messages.content: "I think this place is technically called Villo? Don't often have reason to call it by name. We're in Weath. In Arctica, obviously."

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She furrows her brows.* "There is no country named Arctica."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "The circumstances of my arrival are unusual. You can understand disorientation as to my possessions."

author.name: pichuis

author.name: pichuis

author.name: scipe

messages.content: "Detective Fainda Shinjitsu. I'm investigating this murder."

author.name: pichuis

author.name: pichuis

messages.content: "Yes, that would be me. I'll be polite and not ask about the fake name."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "You knew Oku, correct? Are you familiar with his death?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Yes."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She takes a seat at the table, assuming there is one free.* "Was Oku his real name, or a nickname?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: She takes a breath. "Not his legal name."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "What was his legal name?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Why?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I am attempting to locate him in the census data for this area to confirm its veracity."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I don't know anything about the census data."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I do not recall asking about the census data. I asked what his legal name was."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I think that if your ultimate concern is with the veracity of the census data, you'd do well to take it up with someone other than me. ...I don't know Oku's name."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "But you knew it was not his legal name?" *She looks at her curiously, then skips ahead three pages after Jojo's and labels that page for Diana Fetcher, writing down "socialite", "smoker", "made time for "more queer folk"", "discovered the body of Oku", "said Oku was not his legal name, claimed not to know what it was".*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "When did you discover his body?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "...Would've been today, two hours past sunrise. 8 AM, maybe."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "What did you do after that?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She's having an enthralling conversation by PDA.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I yelled out for someone to come over. It was clear he was already dead, though. I just didn't know what exactly to do."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Who came over?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "First one to come over? Oku's neighbor, I think."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "John?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She looks vaguely annoyed at typing her own message.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I don't know him."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "What are you even doing with that thing?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I'm sending messages."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Odd."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Are you unfamiliar with the device?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "This is a phone, a wireless device used for communication."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Never heard of it."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Tell me what year it is."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "917. You hit your head, Fainda?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Did you?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Is the 917 you claim to be in 917 BC or AD 917?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "What?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Before Christ and anno Domini. If you claim to be unfamiliar with those terms, that indicates neither of the two."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "The year I last lived in is 2022 AD. This device originates from that era."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Hm." She seems less surprised by this than by just saying the years, somehow.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "BC and AD are also referred to as BCE and CE. Time travel is impossible, so if your claim was the truth and we were both alive, we would be living in a time after the Common Era, or where its use was outdated."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Allow me to humour you. What event marks the beginning of your calendar system at the year 0, and how long does one year last?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I'm not a historian, kid. Maybe the country's founding? A year's 52 weeks. 52 weeks exactly this time around."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "You are almost correct. How many days are in a week, how many hours are in a day, how many minutes are in an hour, and how many seconds are in a minute?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Why are you in my house?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "To discover the truth."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "My goal is to solve this murder. I aim to conduct this investigation normally, but if you insist on a contradictory account of reality, I have no choice but to pursue it."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content:
She stands up. "I tolerate a wide variety of different people, but I can't abide by hypocrisy. You're not going to get away with branding me as a liar when you go by a fake name, make up a fake year, and pretend to be affiliated with the law."

She extends her arm and points at you. "Who are you?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Are you calling me a sinner?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I don't care what anyone's god thinks. This is about my own judgement."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She pulls out her crossbow and notches a bolt.* "My name is Fainda Shinjitsu. I am Japanese. Nihonjin. The year I come from is 2022, and the electronic device I used provides evidence to that effect, unless you have another explanation for its origin. I am a private detective, and I never claim to be affiliated with any government."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I never called you a liar. You'll find that in a murder investigation, '2 conflicting truths' just means that an investigator is making a mistake. I work carefully to ensure no mistake is mine."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Hah. You mad someone killed a guy in this village before you could? Shoot me if you dare."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She stares at Diana with a face of frustration.* "I had no intent to kill an innocent man. Can you say the same?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I never killed anyone."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I never asked if you did. Are you unable to understand the difference between 'anyone' and a sinner?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Only that the latter is a more exclusive category. One you don't seem too fond of."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "To hide facts, to shun the truth for a lie... that is the mark of a sinner."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "The supernatural and omnipresent are, themselves, not real. The one absolute truth is reality, and so to refuse it is sin."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Where is this sin, oh wise one?" She smirks.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *Fainda now looks at her with disgust before tilting her crossbow up and firing at the ceiling.* "Will you refuse to give up the truth?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "If you do not see yourself as a sinner, answer my questions with that truth. Refusing to answer only makes your claims more suspicious."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "How long are minutes, hours, days, weeks, and months? What country, continent, and planet do you live on? What calendar system do you use? Would you ever be willing to kill an innocent man if given the opportunity to?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "60 seconds, 60 of those, 24 of those, 7 of those, and that last one isn't a real word. Arctica. The normal one. By definition, no. Do you have a warrant?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She faintly smirks.* "I do. What continent is the country of Arctica on, and what planet is that continent on? Do you claim they share the name Arctica?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I think you're full of shit, show me it. I don't know what you're talking about. Most people will just say 'the world', but researchers have some fancy term for the wider expanse Arctica exists on. Geo-something."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I do not currently hold a physical document which states the existence of power legally provided to me. I do, however, possess the authorisation which makes up a warrant."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "An ego, then. Great."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I hold no selfish desires. You may find that difficult to understand."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Who founded Arctica?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "You're a funny one. I know Aldoah united the land, but I don't know if he really formally established the kingdom. Seemed more like a warlord from what I remember learning."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Don't know who the first king was. Don't really care."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "What political system do you follow now? Is Arctica still a kingdom?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Uh, yeah."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She pauses for a moment, feeling off-track.* "Have you always lived here? How often do people travel to and from Arctica?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I was born in the province capital, but I've always lived in Arctica. I don't know a single person who came from somewhere outside Arctica, but there's surely some."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "In that case, I must request your opinion on the murder. You may recall the wound on Oku's corpse. It was thoroughly burnt, as if extreme, directed heat was applied specifically to that area."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I think that's pretty fucked up, and a terrible way to go. I hope the criminal doesn't get away with it. I don't know what else you want from me."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Your cooperation is important."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "What do you believe could be able to cause such a wound fitting the level of technology known to you? A more advanced weapon such as a flamethrower may be out of the question."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Some kinda fire sword, I suppose? I've never seen anything that could do that, no."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I don't believe a 'fire sword' would be a practical weapon or easy to create."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Don't you think practicality is a non factor here? If you wanted to kill someone, the hole in the torso would be enough by itself. The only reason for the extra mutilation of the body would be some kind of sick mind."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Perhaps they did, but the sword would burn its own grip before causing such complete damage."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Obviously it would be made to not do that."

author.name: scipe

messages.content:
**Jojo (Real name Unknown)'s Logic**
*Actually just relaying the logic of others*

"The way Oku was killed is considerably brutal. Unnaturally so."

"He died pierced by something that burned him at the same time."

"There is no known weapon to any of those asked which can cause such effects."

"The Pale One has an as of yet unconfirmed method of killing others."

"In addition, the amount of traces left on the scene were minimal."

"There are possible signs of forced entry, but no evidence that a single human other than Oku was in the house."

"Not even any blood, and Oku was supposedly a quite powerful fighter who would not go out without struggling."

"The Pale One has no hair to lose, no skin to shed, no blood to bleed. It's flesh, if it can even be called that, is entirely uniform."

"A 'silent killer', evidence-ways."

"Finally, the motive."

"Nobody disliked Oku."

"Monsters are known to act violently for no discernible reason; no need for a personal connection or even acting for survival."

"That's about it, I think."

*Completed*

messages.content:
**Fainda's Logic**

"Several hours ago, I awoke to meet the white-skinned creature you see before you today. Its appearance contradicted reality, but it identified itself as Blanche, and demonstrated an ability to drain colour from objects. Hours later, I learned of the existence of John, the man who led you down the path to suspect it and the neighbour of Oku. You may believe that man and that creature have no further connection, but that belief is far from the truth. Blanche and John are accomplices."

"You recall the unusual injury inflicted on the victim. He was stabbed to the abdomen and his wound was severely burned. You assumed that the victim was pierced by a weapon that simultaneously burned him, but there was no evidence to prove that the burning and stabbing occurred simultaneously. John chose to present that narrative as fact so that the populace would view the murder as supernatural. As I deduced, Oku was stabbed with a normal weapon. He fell to the ground, where his wound touched a normal heated object, posthumously searing it."

"Inside his house, a window was very slightly cracked. Its back door was forced open when the body was discovered, but the less obvious clue was unnoticed. This was how the murderer, John, entered. Blanche never had a chance to enter the building, but John saw an opportunity and climbed through. He flipped the corpse before escaping and concocted a scheme in that moment to frame an easy target and remove suspicion from any human. His original plan was to frame George Tanaka, who had opportunity and who the settlement was naturally predisposed against as an apparent foreigner, but taking advantage of the lies of folklore was easier and more enticing."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content:
"In reality, what appears to be an entity beyond imagination is a hologram projected by an orbital satellite. John chose to prey on local superstition surrounding The Pale One to provide a scapegoat, avoiding any suspicion for his crime. The belief in the myth of its existence corrupts the minds of those who fear it, subconsciously causing them to perceive it as tangible. John's motivation is uncertain, but jealousy is likely. John was less known than even Oku. As an unknown and unwanted sinner, John was spiteful to Oku, and would choose to stage the crime to gain validation from 'solving' it and feed his own hero complex."

"The hologram needed to move autonomously. John created an artificial intelligence to control it. The holographic construct was placed in a well-painted cave which acted as a 'psychiatric hospital', and the cave's walls and floors were implanted with further holographic technology to allow it to fully function inside the cave. it was not a coincidence that Blanche left the cave on the same night that he was suspected of a murder. The intelligence was given a backstory where it was shunned and attacked, but John met it and instructed it through pantomime to leave the cave at the next opportunity. I was placed inside, unconscious, as further encouragement, pushing it to follow me once I left."

"After Blanche was left alone, the artificial intelligence span from control and gained a complete mind and set of desires. It was unable to speak so that it could not defend itself, but it broke free from that restriction with the new freedom. John's surprise was genuine. It maintained its sin as an accomplice out of fear of being discovered to be complicit in the murder, and once it arrived to the settlement, it continued to follow me and watch my investigation because it felt that fear in its naïveté, before being 'discovered' as the conclusion to the scheme, not knowing following that step would doom it anyway."

messages.content:
“What” Blanche speaks first.

The crowd murmurs in what mostly seems to be confusion.

John smirks. “So you’re throwing an accusation at me, are you? I’ll admit it. The Pale One probably doesn’t exist.”

“What” Blanche.

“But everything else in your little story… is nothing but your own delusions. Tell me, you wannabe Finder. How closely have you checked the *front* door of Oku’s house?”

messages.content:
**John’s Logic**

“Finder here has seen the proof herself; that she could enter Oku’s house at all!”

“I’m sure you won’t take anything I say at face value, so I’ll mention here what can be verified. There’s only *one* key to every house in Villo. And within the internal mechanisms of his front door’s lock, I bet you’ll find a significant amount of dust. Because Oku *doesn’t lock his front door!* He keeps the key in his house. And this is known. There hasn’t been a single theft, let alone murder, in the entire recorded history of this settlement. Around here, not locking your doors is the default. Only a few people do it. Diana’s paranoid, maybe she does. There would not be a reason for someone to not use the front door.”

He switches to a thinking pose.

“Now, let’s consider the state of the body. It was in the *kitchen*. And there were no blood traces anywhere else. We can assume, then, that he was killed right there. He was *awake*. He must have seen the killer coming. Yet, upon seeing this person outside his back door, he made no attempt to invite them in, already knowing they were up to no good. From the clear lack of familiarity our culprit has with how this community operates to the behavior we can deduce of the victim, the culprit *had* to have been someone not from here.”

“I’m going to return to our interloper’s purported sequence of events. She immediately dismisses the idea of a weapon that can inflict heat. And for what reason? Because one was not found? True, evidence is important. So go ahead, Finder! Produce this unknown heated object! Produce the device capable of projecting illusions of beasts! Or can you not do that?”

He makes the smug shrug head shake pose.

“Personally, I think you *can* show us evidence that settles things. The murder weapon itself, kept in your very own home! With such a valuable item, you wouldn’t dispose of it unless you were certain you needed to.”

author.name: scipe

messages.content:
"Aha. John is clearly unable to resist attempting to take advantage of his target's status as an apparent foreigner, just as I explained." *She turns back to John and smirks.* "Do you recall your goal? I explained that you were originally planning to frame George Tanaka. From the perspective of this settlement, George Tanaka is a foreigner. He may have conducted a census, but he would have no knowledge of this settlement's precise customs. Likewise, Blanche is a foreigner, and would clearly have no knowledge of when Villo's doors were locked. And, right now, you're attempting to use my status as a foreigner, with no other evidence, to call me the killer. Your intention is transparent. If you intended to frame them, you would choose to forcibly enter through the back door to contribute to this narrative, as you did."

"Perhaps I assume too highly of your intelligence? You may wish to dismiss my argument as conjecture, but yours is significantly less well-founded. Do you truly believe that Oku, already a loner, would be able to immediately tell a foreigner from a resident through the window of his back door? I shall remind you that George Tanaka conducted his census successfully, and was apparently able to obtain the necessary information from Oku without incident. Despite this, you assume that he would immediately see a foreigner as suspicious."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content:
"The murder likely occurred at night. In a case involving a break-in, few common criminals with endless time to commit their crime would choose not to use the cover of darkness to avoid detection, and using it makes identifying them through a window significantly more difficult. Forcing open the door and stepping inside could produce enough noise to wake him up, a fact which easily rebuts your logic by itself. Indeed, if your sequence of events was accurate, why would he not take any weapon, such as a knife, to defend himself? None was found. Even if the murderer chose to commit their crime at day, believed the door was locked, and was unobservant enough not to notice they could simply enter freely, why would they choose to break in from the back door? If they were truly unknown to him, they would have no reason not to knock and wait for him to answer. In reality, John already knowing the murderer was dangerous clearly points to him being familiar with them. Picture this scene. John notices a suspicious figure outside his front door, that of his sinner neighbour. Wary of the neighbour, he senses the figure has ill intent. He has no time to take the key to lock the door, but knows that, as part of the settlement, they would simply open the door, so he runs to the door and physically holds it shut, pulling the handle with his strength. The murderer, unable to easily enter, moves to the back door and forces the lock open. John runs to confront him, but, having had no time to take a weapon, is stabbed and dies."

"You have no evidence that I killed John beyond a racial profile, and the concept is absurd. I have no connection to John. I entered 'Arctica' when I woke up in a cave today, the same cave that Blance was placed inside. I come from Japan, as I have repeatedly stated. You would not find a house on this continent connected to me, or a record of my existence. Which of the two possibilities sounds more plausible to you? All paths lead to a long-term resident."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content:
"Furthermore, I never intended to entirely dismiss the idea of a weapon that can inflict heat, but merely state that you asserting its use as fact was unsubstantiated, and my hypothesis is far more likely to have occurred. Are you capable of producing a weapon able to produce such an extreme heat as to near-instantly produce such a scar by way of a stab performed with it? Any such weapon would be extremely unconventional, and its use would be unnecessary to kill. You have not named a store where you would purchase a weapon as impractical as a 'fire sword', or named the components you would use to assemble a tool with that quality. An orbital satellite is, as its name suggests, orbital. Due to its location, size, and complexity, it would be impossible for me to physically produce it. Your request is blatantly impossible."

"Your representations of my arguments are disingenuous, only natural for a sinner attempting to escape justice for his crime. The unknown heated object we referred to was taken from the scene. I believed you disposed of it, but if you would apply your 'logic' while committing murder yourself, perhaps you should show us the object used to burn the corpse, kept inside your very own home?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content:

The old man from before speaks up, looking at you. "I don't get it, though. Doesn't George live here?" The crowd mumbles about George Tanaka.

If we conducted a survey of this crowd, we could learn how many believed George Tanaka to live here."

messages.content: "When I talked to you, you told me you knew Oku wasn't the victim's legal name. You also told me you didn't know what it was. I thought at that moment that your claim was implausible. I was correct."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "You were aggressive towards me as a matter of deception. You knew with certainty, based on what has been revealed, that me pursuing the subject of his name was a matter of importance. I was attempting to uncover the truth, which, as a sinner, you naturally found undesirable."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I respected the man's desire to keep his identity secret." Diana has calmed down.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "You disrespected my efforts as a detective. You acted as if you saw my investigation as fraudulent."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "This respect was my error. I should have realized such a thing would lead to problems in the understanding others have of the case."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I never respected your efforts as a detective, and I still do not. It's amazing to me that these people are all listening to you."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Your 'lack of respect' was built on nothing. You saw me enter the house pursuing the trail behind a claim you knew for a fact was a lie, and ask the person who knew the truth what it was. From the moment you met me, you knew I was competent."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "This is irrelevant to me. My point is that your attitude was caused by the act of hiding your identity. You already 'admitted' that you knew Oku's real name, but you still refuse to admit the truth of your identity, your real motivator."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: “I’m Diana Fetcher. You want my fuckin’ birth certificate?” She snaps her pipe in half. “They’re the same guy! A different outfit, some cosmetics, and you go from the local unassuming old guy to an unaccountable foreigner who can be as rude as he needs to! You’re welcome.”

messages.content: *She laughs.* "You functionally admitted, while Oku, George Tanaka, and Diana Fetcher were treated as separate entities, that revealing they lived together would significantly affect the latter man if he was alive. You now attempt to reverse your course the moment people begin to notice you were Oku."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "This assertion is ludicrous. Why would he possibly do this, besides to act rudely while talking to people annually at most? How would he disguise his voice? If Oku's real, legal name was George Tanaka, then why would the man leading a double-life not record his other name in his own census data?"

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "'Oku', the farmer, was alone. There was no reason to choose to live as him, yet you implied George Tanaka was the original name.
