messages.content:
The back of the note contains the following.

> *To whom it may concern,*
> 
> *I'm banking on this being found first by someone else, and that someone else knowing that paper has two sides. Or on that idiot "detective" not knowing that fact and discarding this if she finds it first.*
> 
> *My name is Diana Fetcher, and I am leaving Villo. I have not been subtle about this, but I have no attachment to this community. I am here because after failing out of the central academy, this was the only place I could even attempt to afford. None of you have liked me, and I'm fine with that. I don't like you either.*
> 
> *I suppose I'll have to be homeless now, but that's unavoidable. I am running because I have been subjected to blackmail. It is infuriating to watch that woman grill me for the lies I didn't tell, but here's everything I hid.*
> 
> *George Tanaka and Oku are the same person. George Tanaka did something early in his time here that soured everyone's opinion of him, and after he did a faked "leaving", he came back as the newly born simple farmer.*
> 
> *I am aware of this, of course, because my occupation has led me to being in private with him fully exposed and unable to hide his appearance. I'm sure those I never interacted with suspected this anyway. Congratulations on figuring that out, idiots.*

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
> *George Tanaka was murdered a week ago. On that occasion, having planned to meet him myself, I saw an old man running out of his house. He had clear murderous intent. I protected my body. He told me he was with the government, providing proof of this, and that he would torment and then murder me if I spoke of him. The man fled in the direction of the capital.* 
> 
> *A final note, mostly unrelated to the rest, but I suppose since I'm leaving here I should mention it. There's a scavenged teleportation rune in the closet. I raided an airship once, and selling what I took is why I have only had to resort to my career recently. There is a woman living on that structure, and she is very dangerous. Do not use that carelessly.* 
> 
> *Believe me or don't. It doesn't particularly matter, since none of you will ever see me again. I only wish for what little information I can provide to bring a swift end to this case without any tedious "mystery-solving".* 
> 
> *"From Diana Fetcher". That's what it would be proper to put, right? But nobody gave a shit about Diana Fetcher. I'll be someone else now. People listened to that detective, for reasons I'll never understand. Maybe I should act more like that?*

messages.content:
The man identified as an officer sighs. "Clearly we need to have people stationed closer to here. I was prepared for 'just' a murder case today." 

He looks around.

"Everyone in this building right now is going to be treated as a suspect. The woman who goes by 'Fainda Shinjitsu' is additionally suspected of breaching civilian investigative jurisdiction,"

Gats smirks.

"With the knowing assistance and enabling of Gats Beagle."

Gats stops smirking.

"A search warrant is being put out for Diana Fetcher, who also has exhibited suspicious behavior related to the murder. Her face is going to be all over town guards' mail for the nearest 300 miles. I am going to ask all of you to come with me or jeopardize your innocence."

Oishi mentioned higher ups being concerned about this case. But for what he’s doing right now, the immediate securing of the crime scene? That’s just whoever is closest. He’s provincial.”

messages.content: “Prisoners are kept in… prison? Civilian investigative jurisdiction would involve the actions appropriate for a person to carry out related to the handling of the crime, assuming no additional attributes of that person. I’m slightly different as someone licensed in law, so violations by me would be handled as something else. Stuff like restraining the killer fleeing the scene is completely justified, and then there’s greyer areas like independently checking something that may not be possible to check by the time the proper authorities arrive. You’ve got a chance with most stuff, but I don’t know if there will be any way out of breaking down the door. This is all assuming you’re tried as a person at all, the opposing counsel might try to mess with that if you can’t provide proper ID.”

messages.content:
She sighs. “I value ‘perfection’ in investigations I supervise, or am *supposed* to supervise. I prefer not to make theories pre-emptively, but were I to explain my current thoughts…”

She turns towards Rikarasu. “The location seems incredibly significant. It is neither the easiest nor most secure place to hide a body, and we already reasoned it’s more likely they were placed rather than killed here. I’m tempted to say this is some kind of cult activity, but without a solid grounding of a group that might do something like this, I might be falling for a deliberate impression staging things this way was meant to create. I guess I’ll look into ‘alternative religion’ just in case.”

She rests her hand on her cheek, then balls it into a fist. “The only other way for the location to matter I see is if it was somehow more practical than any other location for the perp, which would place the most suspicion on anyone who works or has worked here. That’s probably also something we need to check.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Her expression hardens. “…Why am I leaking this to you, anyway…?”

messages.content: *Fainda looks at her with a prideful expression halfway to a smirk.* "Why not? I also aim for perfection. Understanding the ideas of other investigators is important to that."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I agree that theorising at this stage is pre-emptive. However, the placement of the bodies does catch my interest. Regardless of the reason, the location must have been practical enough for them to actually place the bodies without being detected, almost certainly over multiple, or even dozens, of visits. That implies that they had a position here, as you suggested, or that they were able to avoid entering when anybody else would enter. They could also have another way of accessing the area below the floorboards, besides simply repeatedly lifting them up. A tunnel, for example, could be used to enter that space or to slot the babies in."

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content:
Yasu mutters something about twists as you leave.

Alicia opens the door. "Hello?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Hello. Are you free?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I guess?" She closes the door behind her and steps outside. She looks tired.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I wish to ask you a few questions."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Were you troubled by the police for long?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Well, only a few hours yesterday, but I don't think they're done with me."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I am curious about the 'letter' you apparently sent to alert law enforcement."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "What was in it?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Uhhh... I'unno. Something like, there's something in the shrine, check it out please. And then I signed concerned citizen."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She raises her eyebrows.* "Did you learn any further information about the case after you left me?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Nah. It was a lot of the resta the cops catching up to you and Kyros."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Are you sure? In particular, you didn't see the police talking to anyone other than you and themselves?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Not at the shrine, nah. I don't think they had any other witnesses or such."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "That would appear logical, considering the timing. It seems you have no relevant details, so that is all from me."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She backs out and walks to and into her house.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "...Huh. Should I have done more there?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "It obviously would've made sense to be upfront, but this still feels risky. Am I being too... evasive, lately?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "That's no good technique for a detective of logic! But I did want to talk to Yasu then. It's only responsible to tell my 'investigative partner' about something like this, after all."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "And now he's suddenly Haruka Tanaka's son?" *She laughs.* "What kind of coincidence is that?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Actually... isn't that suspicious? They both contacted me to work 'with' me. They have different last names, they both sought me out apparently independently, but they're parent and child."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Could they be colluding? I already knew she had a son, but his name was Ichigo Culbasko. Not... Yasuyasu Miyamoto. And there's George Tanaka. Tanaka is a very common last name, but the timing really makes me wonder if they're connected somehow."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She freezes up momentarily as if suddenly making a connection.* "Wait... Culbasko? Ichigo Culbasko and Zaquera Culbasko! Of course!"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: https://tenor.com/view/mindblown-explosion-shook-shock-explode-gif-7721542

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

thumbnail.url: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\mindblown-explosion-28288.png

video.url: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\mindblown-explosion-7BEB6.mp4

messages.content: "...What does that even mean? It can't just be more coincidence, can it? Caaan it?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Ha! I'll give this an answer! This is exactly what I need!"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Well, speaking of what I need..." *She goes to the kitchen and makes some lunch. It's the same as yesterday's.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: While in the midst of lunch, Rikarasu loses consciousness. Chapter 3 ends.

author.name: scipe

messages.content: ((WHAT))

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: ((1984 gif you cannot finish lunch))

author.name: zzazz
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\00e5cb55aacbe3824e8b8a9d53aac811-1CCD0.png

messages.content: Rikarasu wakes up in a room she does not recognize. Gats Beagle is there, writing some things down.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: (( @pichuis ))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

mentions.name: pichuis
mentions.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She glances around the room quickly and stares at Gats.* "What? Where am I?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Oh, you're awake. Well, this is a holding cell. We're in the capital of Weath, for now."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Ah."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "...How are you feeling?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Fine. I'm much more worried about you. You slept over a full day, y'know. The initial trial already happened."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "That's ridiculous."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "What happened in the carriage?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Nothing, really. You fell asleep at some point. Then we arrived. They tried to wake you up but failed."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She searches through her pockets.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: She has everything she had on her in Arctica before sleeping there.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "And... what happened in the 'initial trial'?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Well, not much good. For me, at least. I appealed enough to keep things going, but they're deadset on putting the blame on me. It's bizarre. I talked a bit with investigators earlier on, and they seemed interested in exploring various possibilities, but by a certain point the party line was that I did it, no questions asked."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I imagine wherever things go next, you'll probably be asked to testify."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "The party line..."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "What connection do you have to the murder? I had no hint that you were related whatsoever, but surely they have at least a trace of evidence against you?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I indirectly aided your investigation, that whole thing which they weren't too happy about. But the fact that you don't exist means you have no motive. The opposition spun a tale about why I might want to kill him, and then how I could have manipulated the scene to hide my presence."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I was under the impression that 'not existing' was simply a legal construct to strip individuals of rights."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I exist, and you can see me sitting here right now. Correct?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Yeah, unless we want to get all philosophical. But even if we replace it with more accurate terminology, the point stands. What reason could you have to kill? Nobody's ever even seen you before."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "What reason could you have?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "The story is that, since they have evidence I was involved in a rather dogmatic religious group early in my life, I killed him because I suspected him of sexual infidelity. Which is just insane, and feels like the first thing they could come up with. I imagine that's why I could hold out despite the odds. They could do a lot better at rigging things against me."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Hmph."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "'Nobody' having seen me before makes me immediately suspicious. If a strong motive is such an issue, I would have expected them to investigate my 'true' identity."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "They did try that, at first. But at some point, discussion of that stopped. I guess they gave up? I've thought about trying to shift blame to you, but it would've felt a bit too scummy while you weren't even able to defend yourself. ...Not that I plan to do so now, or anything."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "What happens now, then? When is the next trial?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I don't know. Maybe today. They don't want this case taking too long. But I might've bought some time for me to think by demanding this be brought to a higher court."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "And as for the charge of 'breaching civilian investigative jurisdiction'? What came of that?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I guess that's low priority. They might try it at a later date. Or you could be absolved of it depending on what is decided on the murder."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "How so?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "The ends justifying the means, or something. This case has become something of a public spectacle. They might risk backlash if someone supposedly working to stop the killer is penalized."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I hope so."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Perhaps now you see how foolish it is to aid corrupt authorities which will betray you the moment it becomes convenient for them."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "It was a mistake getting involved in this god damn case."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "It was no mistake for me."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Do you have any real plan?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *I pull out the PDA and send a message in the gc.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "My plan is to buy enough time to find out what is motivating them. That's all I can do."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "What are you doing now, before the trial?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Taking and reviewing notes. I'm just wondering if there's something I've missed in all this."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "You are more familiar with your country's systems, but from my perspective, the issue is all too commonplace. Law enforcement, prosecutors, and governments may push for an easy verdict over exposing the truth. In such a 'public spectacle' of a case, a quick resolution is likely all they desire."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She glowers.* "If an organisation is willing to shun the truth for sin even once, their motivations are unpure."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: He sighs. "It's not unheard of. Really I'm just baffled that whatever corruption exists is so subtle. Usually there's an obvious party of wealth and influence involved, but I have no idea who could have any stake in this. George Tanaka worked for the government, but not in a very major capacity. And everyone else who is in Villo can't afford to live anywhere better. If it's just a desire to get the case over with, why were they so thorough with the initial investigation?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "This is a markedly unconventional case. The presence of a white monster, a completely unknown foreigner, a disguised victim, and an impersonating witness all add up to create a case difficult to solve and with several real candidates, whether to suspect or frame."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Is it possible that somebody with a higher position held a grudge against George Tanaka?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I doubt it. I looked into that, but in terms of his career, the guy's spotless. Went above and beyond in his responsibilities wiithout even asking for so much as a raise. Any grudge someone would have against him would be smaller scale and personal, and I couldn't find anything about his personal life."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She thinks.* "...Who would have the power to influence the investigation like this?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Only the chieftain on the provincial level. But if we open up the suspects to elsewhere, it could be someone wealthy, or anyone involved with federal government and monarchy."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Oh, I was gonna mention if we ever talked again. I'm not familiar with things further West, but I checked with an associate, and there actually is a similar case that exists to your proposed idea of separating from a province. It involved a lot of money, though."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "How much?"

author.name: pichuis

messages.content:
"On the day that the body was discovered, I arrived at the settlement of Villo and learned that a killing had occurred."

"I visited houses identified as belonging to Oku, Diana Fetcher, and Arnoldamaezza Goititmythate, in co-operation with an individual who identified themselves as Jojo."

"I examined the body and the area around it, heard the testimony of Diana Fetcher, and obtained a copy of census data from Arnoldamaezza Goititmythate."

"After that point, residents of the village had agreed that a supposed supernatural pale monster, Blanche, was responsible."

"Watched by a large crowd, including Jojo, I argued with a man named John, who led them to this solution, and deduced a more plausible answer."

"As i attempted to escort Diana Fetcher until law enforcement arrived, she escaped, punched me, and fled to her home. I chased after her with a small group in tow."

"Together, our group broke down the door to her house and searched for Diana Fetcher. I discovered a hidden note left to taunt me, and another individual discovered markings on the ground of closet."

"Diana Fetcher, however, was not found. I gathered everyone present and asked them to inform carriage operators of the incident, at which point "Jojo" entered and identified himself as Gats Beagle. Law enforcement entered quickly thereafter and arrested us."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content:
"This matches with the information of our investigation, more or less." A man wearing a guard uniform says this.

"And what of this 'co-operation' more specifically?" The judge asks.

"I showed her relevant locations, answered questions about the town! Nothing th-" The judge bangs a gavel and stares at Gats.

"As you were." He looks at Rikarasu.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
"When I met, he told me he was "trying to figure out the actual witnesses" himself. He informed me of the murder, provided information about the town, and directed me to a nearby shop, at my request."

"After I was directed to the victim's house by a stranger and investigated that house, I found him eavesdropping outside. He asked me about what I had discovered and directed me to Arnoldamaezza Goititmythate, the man known as Booksmith."

"That man then directed me to Diana Fetcher's house. I returned to Oku's house after conversing with her, and he alerted me that members of the village had arrived at an answer and explained the logic they used. We walked to the site they had gathered at together."

"This was the extent of our investigative co-operation."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content:

"That's *absurd!* This is a mockery of a justice system, gravitating all evidence towards my persecution! Would you arrest a *map* if she found one? How could I have known--"

The door slams open. An unfamiliar man screams the following.

messages.content:
Upon staring at the writing in arcane symbols, Rikarasu experiences a first person memory from the perspective of, based on the place they are standing, Shkeep. Shkeep looks up to see Rikarasu Endo holding a map.

"That'll be an insignificant amount." Shkeep mutters.

"How much for this map?" Rikarasu asks.

"One gold." Shkeep replies.

Rikarasu hands over a single gold piece. "I would like a receipt." 

"What?" Shkeep is confused.

Rikarasu looks slightly annoyed. "A printed record of my purchase. Where I live, it is common practice to be able to provide one."

Shkeep turns away.

The vision ends.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Tdychrufhfudjheueueehwtttwhat?" *She falls into a momentary daze despite the harmlessness of the receipt-cutaway.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She comes to her senses staring at the shopkeeper.* "*What* did you *do* to this paper?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: ((let me check something for one second))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: ((ok yeah))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I didn't do anything. Just had our accountant create a record. Isn't that what you wanted?" Shkeep looks behind you. There's kind of an impatient line of people.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "What record? Exactly *what* do these symbols mean?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I don't know. Ask him." Shkeep waves in the direction of the person Shkeep talked to.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She runs to that person.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "What did you do?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Huh? Do what?" This accountant is a man dressed in generic era-appropriate attire with short hair and an exhausted expression.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She sounds exasperated.* "What did you do to that paper?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "It's a minor illusion that interfaces with a person's memories to, at least in theory, create an accurate record. Did the way Shkeep saw things offend you or something? I can't exactly be blamed for that." He's idly writing down on a clipboard as he talks to you.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: ""Illusion"? How could you possibly "interface" with someone's memories and create an illusion from some *symbols*?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "It's a basic application of psychological magic. I'm only really capable of enough to facilitate my job specifically." He places his hand on his head. "Look, I've already had a shitty day, and they're already gonna be docking my pay for taking time off, which *wasn't* even my fault. Could you get to the point so I can resolve this and not end up in even more hot water? What exactly is your problem with this?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Psychology could do nothing like this, and magic doesn't exist! This is impossible!"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: He looks at you funny. "Are you an associate of a *Mr. Richard Ogden*?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "No?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "...Why do you ask that?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Just weird when something happens to you for the first time and then you see it happen again just a little later. Hard to believe they're unrelated. He denied the existence of magic too." He looks up from his papers. "Is there a particular reason you believe it isn't real? I didn't bother dealing with Ogden, but now I'm curious."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I have never before witnessed any "magic". The fictitious conception of magic is an affront to the laws of reality. It defies all logic."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "How could you possibly 'perform' magic? How could an arbitrary set of symbols written by humans perform a supernatural miracle?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Okay. So this thing you just saw -- it's not real because you haven't seen it. And it's also not real because it can't be real? I can't really dispute that, then." He's looking a little smug.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "What? You...!"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *Deep breaths.* "You asked me why I believe magic is not real. I saw a vision from somebody else's perspective. Besides that vision, the fact remains that the idea of magic contradicts all common sense."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Another tautology. Something can't be real because it's not something that seems real to...what's your name?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Fainda Shinjitsu."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Wow, a weird name. Completely goes against my common sense. Guess I shouldn't believe you, then. How exactly do you think you're talking to me right now? How did you walk into this store? Why were you even able to communicate to me that you don't understand what just happened? They all seem pretty farfetched to me."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I understand the foundations of science. That is precisely why I know magic contradicts how individuals and objects interact. There is no process I can imagine by which looking at such symbols could intercept the brain in such a manner. There is no manner for it to occur within physical processes."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "If you saw an apple fall up and were told that 'gravity does not exist', would you instantly believe it?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "No, because I've seen apples fall down before. That's not what we're talking about. If I saw an apple fall up, I'd probably believe 'a mechanism to make apples fall up exists'. Claiming gravity does not exist would require an explanation for all prior times."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Anyway, I think if you're claiming magic 'contradicts how individuals and objects interact', you're using some absurd definition. That just seems patently ridiculous to me."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "If an anti-gravity device did exist, it would fit within the rules of gravity as we understand them, or pave the way for a different understanding."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "It is not implausible that, through technological advancement, one could. 'Magic' such as that which this would be is different. It represents interaction entirely outside those rules."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I would agree that magic doesn't fall within the rules of gravity, yes. It's a more general category. The reverse would probably be true."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Perhaps I was quickly knocked out and placed into a hyper-realistic virtual reality, only to be returned inside this shop feeling nothing but slightly dazed. Any other explanation is more plausible, unless you can explain how magic would cohere with all other physical interaction."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I mean, you stopped experiencing the real world and started experiencing a constructed vision, yes. I'm not really sure what your issue is. You're demanding I explain how something was possible and yet you can't tell me what needs explaining."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "How does magic function? Tell me that as you apparently know it."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Well, in general, it's convoluted. I mean, it's everywhere. We're made of magic, or something. You'd be better off checking with an expert. I can explain how I did what I specifically did, if you'd like."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Go ahead."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content:
"Okay."
He rips off a sheet of parchment from a nearby shelf.
"I don't *think* the type of paper or ink should matter, but I've had a way harder time getting anything to work without using a quill." He scrawls down some symbols. "After defining the document as a runic one, this binds the attributes to memories of the past. Do you remember when you first entered this room to talk to me?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Good. That's enough for you to be able to verify this. Though it would be better to have it from your perspective, I can't count on you having given me your real name. Don't want any uncertain factors." He writes down some more iconography. "And...." He looks up from the paper before writing one more symbol. "There! Should work. Because of the properties of runes, this sort of thing is allowed to exist. Explanation over." He stares expectantly at Rikarasu with the note left on his desk.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "...Ugh." *She grabs the paper and stuffs it in her pocket without giving it a proper look.*

author.name: pichuis

messages.content: "Are you familiar with the idea of nominative determinism?"

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: “That sounds like a sentiment I’ve heard around. People’s personal destiny. Wyrd and all that. Though getting a job that sounds like your name seems much more mundane.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Literal fate is nothing but superstition."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Nominative determinism refers to the hypothesis that people are attracted to fields connected to their names, often subconsciously."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She smirks.* "On that note, much of what may be attributed to 'destiny' can be traced to confirmation bias and subconscious desires."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: “This feels like another odd quibble. If you redefine fate to be anything that happens for no reason, then yes, it’d be hard to call it real. But I don’t think even the most devout believers think it’s just arbitrary. If it could be disproven entirely by understanding one thing, you’d only have the dumbest people out there subscribing to any of it.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "...What are you talking about?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Tell me, Bonnell. How do you define 'fate'?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: “I don’t particularly care for such things. I’m a number cruncher, yknow. That sentimental stuff only ever leads to disaster with me. But if you asked me what fate means to me…” He stares up at the sky. “I think part of it is the idea that no matter what, there’s always going to be something that happens out of our control. But this makes me think I must be missing something. That’s not worth celebrating at all. The other piece is strange happenstance. The fact that I met you, right after meeting Ogden. Or the fact that you met me, if I happen to turn out to have some unexpected connection from your perspective. This one is obviously a matter of perspective, since you remember when notable things happen more than the infinitely higher amount of mundane occurrences.” He clears his throat. “Or something like that. Wyrd is more specific. It’s about lives of individuals rather than ever implying some universal meaning.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: ((What the fuck are you typing oh my god))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Fate as I see it used is merely escapism without meaning. Do you truly believe that fundamentally, there must always be something outside 'our' control, whether that refers to the control of one individual or the control of humanity? Science has came further than anyone who was alive one-thousand years ago could comprehend in understanding the processes of reality on microscopic levels. One contracting the common cold may fail to understand what sequence of events led to that contraction and at what times, but the events that occur within their body and the manner by which it may have spread to them are all scientifically understood far more than they would take the time to consider. It would be wrong to say that the infection was unavoidable, and thus that it was out of their control, even if modern society lacks mechanisms by which to fully avoid it. Few processes cannot be understood in such a manner, and so cannot have control exerted over. Within the unalienable laws of our world and the limitations of physicality, there is essentially nothing that is 'out of our control' on an unalienable level. Those who flee from that fact and attempt to take solace in a lack of control simply engage in blind cowardice. Any sinner chooses to shun the truth for their own ends, and in the process limits themselves and their own potential. It is by understanding the truth that the world may function; all else is self-defeating. Knowing this is what has led to all true progress to this point. In particular, believing in 'fate' is entirely self-defeating. By believing that no better outcome may be achieved due to unavoidable happenstance, one both refuses to face reality and refuses to seek a better outcome. Even the 'strange happenstance' you discuss is a form of this. Coincidence obviously exists, but to dismiss a coincidence as 'fate' is to fail to examine the connections and biases that do exist. Both are shallow refusals to understand reality on any deep or genuine level. "

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "To put it simply, all lies are shallow, and to insist on shallowness defeats any potential for growth outside of repentance. Elaborate on Wyrd."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: “If everything has a clear cause possible to understand and control, that should include people. That would make the entire idea of choice or control nothing but a farce, wouldn’t it? Or is this some kind of exceptionalism for life?” He mutters to himself. “It doesn’t really matter. We can’t understand our own existence by nature. That’s undeniably true. Wyrd… is about our existences. Or something. The burdens people are saddled with by their circumstances and what surrounds them from birth. And also what heights they may reach.”

He sighs. “Man, you sound like my kid. I dunno, it’s like riding a bicycle, or whistling. You can try all you want to go into the mechanics, but it always feels like something’s missing beyond the tactile experience of just doing it. I think it involves using the energy in the body, at least on a general level. Like, I sure as hell couldn’t keep that up all day. Though someone trained could manage easy. Bonnell, did you bring this person to me so I could explain this?”

“Not really.”

“I guess this makes some sense. But I can’t get a great read on him. Haven’t gone up against him much.”

“Nope. Unless he’s still hanging around the courtroom. Which I doubt. I mean, Bonnell, why would you go to me? I get it’s a little awkward to approach them yourself, but obviously people on his side are gonna know him better. Ask Joliene, or Solnit if that’s too weird for you.”

“No!” Bonnell yells. “It’s fine. I don’t need anyone. You know damn well I can’t just waltz into the places they live, anyway.”

messages.content:
“There’s nothing to tell!” Bonnell. 

“Unfortunately, Mr. Swansong, I’m your professional partner, not your friend. I’d only prioritize being sensitive to your feelings if you paid extra.”

Bonnell grumbles.

Hirer turns to you, pretending to smile all nice. “Joliene Swansong is a former member of the city guard of Arenda who has recently taken a position under the royal family. She’s also my client’s wife. Soon to be ex. It’s a whole fiasco. Solnit’s another lawyer, though he does a whole bunch of other stuff. Fancies himself a scientist, though if you ask me this split attention only makes him slip up all the more in court. I could get you a chance to speak with either… for a price.”

messages.content:
The processes that allow for such incredible feats are not fully understood, but it is known that almost all modern spells originate from two millennium old tomes (as in, two tomes that are a millenium old) written by someone who went by FATHER MAGIC. Historical opinion is that this was probably a man named Alto Titinius. His explanations were incomprehensible and people learn more elsewhere even when these historically vital works are publicly accessible, but he provided the alchemical and conceptual basis for what people today call ~magic~. Part of it was a matter of confidence; controlled experiment has shown that a wizard who doubts his own capability will have drastically less power behind something like a fireball, even when his ability “should” be the same as someone overly cocky.

Also you CANNOT bring back the dead (1984 gif) or teleport without an absurd amount of practice

messages.content: *She doesn't have much of a justification for asking, but she doesn't have much else to do right now, relatively speaking. She could try to get a job for money, but that does not sound like a fun use of time, unless she finds someone who her detectiving would be useful to, and for that matter she probably should've probed into Bruna's affairs further, but oh well. She could do more research, but finding anything has been difficult, and watching court proceedings is probably more likely to be insightful than most things she could do. She does have the justification that it'd be nice to rest in an actual chair (and she's not new to court-watching), and also she isn't sure what they mean by 'open to witnesses', but she is technically a witness, which is probably good enough for a completely unrelated trial?*
