messages.content: *She sighs.* "I presume *you* hold no personal faith in the truth."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *Admittedly, if her family were Christian, she presumably shook herself out of some indoctrination. But you know what they say: born Shinto, marry Christian and die Buddhist. Because an unintelligent sinner's mind is easily changed by other sinners, or to suit their own ends, or something, or all of the above.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content:
“I believe in the truth. Everyone fuckin’ does. But I doubt it means the same thing for the two of us.”

She sits up. “I think there’s basically three possibilities.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Practically everyone claims to believe in the truth. Many of the same people would lie to a child and feel no remorse."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Go on."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She's still trying to tie Intuition. It doesn't have to be a great knot.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content:
“First one’s the turtle. Y’know, the one that Earth rests on the back of. Some jokers say that it then rests on the back of an even larger turtle, but that’s ridiculous.”

She laughs to herself.

“It’s just a stand-in, though. It’d be pretty complicated for that specifically to be the case in the modern world, since there’s very good reasons to think the world isn’t flat and isn’t resting on anything. But the modern day equivalents of this are what I’m talking about; that conveniently, some all powerful presence has existed just beyond our range of vision for all of human history. I think the way I describe it should indicate I don’t place much stock in that, but it’s a catch-all of people’s crazy ideas that can’t be discounted. You can’t disprove devils or Russel’s Teapot.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "What stops someone from disproving Russell's teapot?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: “Well, nothing’s forever. But most people alive today will probably be dead by the time we can check all our solar system with enough precision to confirm if there’s a teapot floating around.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
“What I think is much more likely is the second idea. The deus ex machina. God from the machine. Simulation theory.”

She waves her hand dismissively. “I’m not such a stickler and AIpocalypse dweeb that I think it’s literally all ones and zeros or whatever. But the arguments for our world being a constructed one are halfway reasonable, and it would indicate the entire question is pointless. Any ‘God’ is beyond our actual reality entirely. And it certainly wouldn’t warrant worship.”

She looks to the side. “I mean, say, fucking, Elon Musk poured enough ill-gotten funds into creating a detailed simulation of a universe. I hardly think that would change anything about him being a jackass subject to the harsh rules of reality.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “It’s just a different set of rules than the ones for whatever he made.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "...And the third possibility?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content:
“Second’s maybe what I consider most likely. But it only takes a shift in perspective to turn it into the third one.”

She grins. “That the only entity worthy of ‘god’ is that which creates everything. The source of all information filtered through its perspective, all that can be known to exist. And from where I’m standing, that’s me.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She scoffs.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "So these are all possible to you? It's unlikely, but certainly possible that an all-power presence created us all, and it's perfectly likely we only exist in a simulation. But it's *impossible* to you that there is no God?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: “That falls into the first category. Sure, there could conveniently be no answer to this question, and everything emerged by magic.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “Don’t fuckin’ lecture me about the Big Bang, by the way. Obviously I mean the pre-existing singularity just came into being for no reason.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Allow me to make my stance clear. It is true that you cannot disprove any of these possibilities, just as you cannot disprove Russell's teapot. But the reason the idea of Russell's teapot was formulated is that it is absurd to treat its existence as the truth. Our brains, and our eyes and ears, the vehicles through which we experience the world, scream to us that existence is simply present as we see it. It came about naturally, by way of the Big Bang, and yes, the pre-existing singularity that came before it came into being 'for no reason'. We have no meaningful evidence to indicate anything otherwise or anything more to the contrary. But it is, indeed, 'possible' that we came from the imagination of a psychopathic greater being. Those possibilities are meaningless, and if you accept those possibilities as likelihoods, the question is meaningless, just as any other question is for the exact same reason."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "The only reason they are ever entertained as possibilities is to distort the truth through their 'unfalsifiability'. A sinner's trick, if you will."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "With that being said, allow me to ask you something. If you believe it is more plausible that, before the Big Bang occurred, the soup of energy that made up the universe was created by a higher being, then where do you believe that higher being could have came from? And if you believe there was a particular source which created that higher being, where do you believe that source came from? And so on."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: She laughs. “Yeah, that’s always the trick. When a christian apologist or what have you says it’s absurd something could have come from nothing, they’re left stammering when you ask what the earlier something came from.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She nods.* "And if you believe we exist in a simulation, where do you believe the 'higher universe' came from? The problem is the same."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: “Then you get turtles all the way down. But I’m not trapped by that kinda thinking.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Oh? And why not?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Do you, pray tell, believe that the universe exists in a time loop, and that it will be created at its end?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: “Ouroboros.” She sneers. “This whole conversation is just killing time, anyway. If I’m god, and a mentally ill one who can’t remember her full potential, I’d stop everything where it stood out of spite.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: ((End session.))

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I very well believe he can."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Tell me, Kamala. What separates *your* 'stupid theories' from mine?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Where do I ever start with a question like that?" She smirks. "They make sense, for one. Backed up by evidence. And I have experience. I know what a perp is and how it walks and talks." She twirls her gun. "I'm sure you won't accept any of those, so maybe the best difference is that they're backed up by physical force."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Perhaps you recall that I was holding a gun up until a few minutes ago."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Does the truth always 'make sense' to you? Does it always fit within your narrow idea of what's reasonable?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Nowadays? Yeah. But of course it isn't always. I had a long time where I had to learn. Trial by fire. That's your problem." She lowers her gun. "You never grow up."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Sure. If I grew up, everything would suddenly *make sense*. Because that's *so* important. Because in real life, experienced detectives simply never make errors, ever."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Has it ever occurred to you that you might just be contorting the truth until it 'makes sense' to you?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Something making sense isn't the same as it being what you already know. I knew you were involved with this case. I didn't know for some time that a different guy named Kyle was connected to it, but that's within the realm of possibility." She shakes her head. "If you're consistently meeting with outcomes that defy all explanation based on your understanding of the world, that's a skill issue."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "*Why* is it an issue?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content:
"It indicates a failure to adapt and understand." She looks back out the window. "I'd have thought people would be here by now..." Kamala mutters.

She turns back to you. "You're like, what, 23? And you've lived in Japan your whole life."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Maybe 'Kyle' has killed them already."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I don't *need* to adapt and understand. I adapt and understand my stances in response to new information. My overall *technique* causes no issues besides frustrating you."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content:
"It causes no issues for *you*, maybe. You're shielded from consequences." 

She turns back towards the window. "I doubt he has killed or ever will kill anyone. He's kind of pathetic." 

Then back to you. "Have you heard this one? 'Great science is built upon the shoulders of giants'. How much do you think humanity would progress if every single person felt the need to reinvent the wheel and prove gravity wasn't upside down each time they did anything?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Little. Luckily, the orientation of gravity is of little relevance to most actions performed."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "It is relevant to nearly all of them."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "*Unless* they have a reason to think otherwise, humans can rely on pre-existing proofs, as they do daily."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Kamala Kyros, would you describe the orientation of gravity as 'relevant' to this confrontation?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Yes. It was pretty relevant when Kyle fell on me earlier, for one. I would accept the theory of gravity being wrong as a last resort with no better possible options. Much like I'd assume you were, what, an imposter or clone of yourself?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Oh, and do you believe I have no evidence for the idea that *you* could be an 'imposter'? I'm afraid you're jumping far too far to reach that conclusion, metaphorically speaking."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "You never do. You didn't have evidence for a mass baby drug overdose. You like to list every conceivable thing that could be the case, prioritizing the most outlandish. Maybe it works for PR, for whatever clients you get. But it doesn't work for me."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I recall telling you that it was too early to jump to conclusions at that point."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Did you have evidence that there was *no* mass baby drug overdose?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Drugs are super fucking illegal in Japan. They are bought and sold within underground markets for lucrative prices. Even if someone were some psychotic serial killer targeting infants, the idea that they were able to procure enough funds with their mental illness for a hundred babies is absurd. It's the ridiculous fearmongering about fentanyl in Halloween candy amped up several orders of magnitude." She rolls her eyes.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Perhaps a swarm of babies *accidentally* inhaled a batch of drugs, and the 'killer' simply hid the evidence after they died."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "What the fuck is a swarm of babies? They're not a pack animal."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "A *horde* of babies. A *large group* of babies. You know exactly what I mean."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I highly doubt there have studies showing the invulnerability of babies against black-market drugs. The idea of 'fenatyl in Halloween candy' came about because of fathers poisoning their children. Would you have dismissed the idea that a child could have been killed by poisoned candy as a result of the myth?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Yes, I do know what you mean, and it makes no sense. You can't start with a conclusion and assume it's a possibility because it meets the bare minimum of being a grammatical phrase. Why were so many babies together? How did they happen to end up in a location with copious amounts of drugs? What drug is possible to accidentally "inhale" en masse?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I hate my higher-ups, Rikarasu. I really do. But compared to a world where someone like you could have the same amount of influence over me, it's not even a contest."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Since the killer was clearly twisted enough to have no problem with concealing murders, perhaps the babies were victims of human trafficking. And since human trafficking is a black-market undertaking, it's only natural they would be stored in the same area as drugs. I imagine a 'white powder' drug such as crack could be inhaled fairly easily by a foolish baby."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Do you understand what the purpose of the dynamic in a court trial is? A defence attorney, and a prosecutor. How could the two arguing help the truth be reached?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "That's not how human trafficking works, you dolt." She rests her hand on her gun. "The idea is conflicting ideas can synthesize so the stronger prevails or they are synthesized into the truth. Though trials tend to be a formality much of the time. In any case, you aren't a prosecutor or defense attorney. You're a third party asking everyone to consider if aliens exist."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I'm a *detective*. Detectives are not a hivemind."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "You're a private investigator. When's the last time you've been called on as a witness for a trial?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "...A few days ago?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content:
"Ha ha." She fake laughs.

"This world is nothing without order. All you've ever done is get in the way of that. I saw the signs, you know. Global tensions rising, PM talking about getting rid of the restrictions you have on the scope of the military. The internet causing an uptick in new types of white collar crime. Privately or publicly funded, this place is on the fast track to a collapse into anarchy."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Your hatred for your higher-ups, your hatred for me, and your description of your co-workers' policing as 'piss-poor' do not paint a picture of someone eager to engage in a battle of wits. If you believe *you're* the only sane person around you, your ideas and expectations can hardly be considered 'normal'."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "A prosecutor and a defence attorney could reasonably have a fierce rivalry, as over-the-top and unlikely as that may seem in reality. A prosecutor holding a defence attorney at gunpoint would be rather unlikely and very unproductive. You think the world is 'nothing without order'? What *could* be more ordered than systematically considering every possibility? The world is nothing without *the truth*. It remains about as complete without your own perceptions of it."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I'm not the only sane person, obviously. I don't like all their methods or ideals, but my co-workers have their heads on straight. Don't act like I think of everyone the way I think of you. I don't hold my co-workers I disagree with at gunpoint."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I've lived through people considering every possibility. For all your faults, I appreciate you being tactful enough to not make a big deal of it, but my name, my appearance, the way I talk... it's obvious I'm not from here. Look into the history of Somalia when you next get the freedom to use a computer. Many people tried *many* different things. That's not order. It's a pseudo-intellectual chaos. You want to consider *every possibility*? There's an infinite amount of those. That consideration process will *be* the result you create."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I really hate you, Fainda. But I hope you can come out of this a better person, in the end."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Rikarasu passes out. ((chapter end and session end!!1))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Rikarasu awakens in a dark room. In the center of the floor is some arcane iconography. The room is otherwise largely featureless, and has one exit.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Also, Yasu is unconscious on the floor. That's a thing.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Uuungh." *She gets to her feet and dusts herself off.* "Once again, perfect timing."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She reaches behind herself and grabs an arrow.* "Hey, Yasu? Ichigo? GET UP!"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content:
He wakes up.

"GAHHHHH!!" He screams. "Where am I?!"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "...Arctica, I would presume, or the real Earth. Somewhere different from the world you are accustomed to, in any case."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "What?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Right now, consider yourself to be in an alternate reality."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She reaches into a pocket and pulls out her own PDA.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Uh." He looks around, backing up to remain close to you.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She thinks.* "Uh... can you read those symbols?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "...No?" He looks wherever you seem to be looking.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She looks at the iconography.* "Perhaps they're cave paintings."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "How did we get in a cave...?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "We were transported here."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "...The last time I was in Arctica, I placed Erica Furuda's body onto a magical teleporter, which transported it to another location, and then stepped on it myself. It was then that I woke up on what appeared to be Earth, and soon afterwards, confronted Haruka Tanaka. Based partially on the suspicious timing of my transportation, I theorised that the 'Earth' I had been transported to was a facsimile of reality, still in Arctica."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "It may instead be that these glyphs are those of a magical timer, which transports us to this area after a certain amount of time passes."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: He sighs, almost calming down a bit from hearing this. "Okay, so if we took that at face value, I'd be an accomplice to this scheme of creating an entire fake version of your everyday life? Some sort of an imposter?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Indeed. But perhaps an unwitting one."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "It could be that you were, in fact, pulled from Earth and then simply brainwashed."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "So why? Why would anyone do that?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "As an attack on me?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "That's a description of it, not a motive."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I struggle to name a precise attacker. It may be that "Intuition Overdrive" planned out this scenario, explaining how he managed to stumble into me on the streets of 'Japan', and set up the timer as part of an escape plan. It may also be that the air vessel's captain orchestrated it, since they would have the ability to set up and modify the teleporter, and... they would have the powers to orchestrate a scenario which would lead me to use the teleporter."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She pockets the PDA, walks up to the exit and opens(?) it.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content:
This next room appears to be floating in a void, but it seems like there are still translucent walls bounding it. 

To the left is another door, and to the right the room continues, becoming brighter and brighter to the point where it can no longer be discerned.

Opposite the door Rikarasu just went through, what appears a giant turtle is floating within the void. There's something beyond the turtle that's hard to make out.

"I'm going to be sick." Ichigoyasu reacts.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "It appears that this animal may be an untamed metaphor." *She walks towards the giant turtle.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She then attempts to pet it.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: Rikarasu cannot reach the turtle.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "By metaphor, I mean 'turtle placed here for a symbolic reason'."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "It may be that this intends to communicate that we are currently outside of Earth, and looking at it being held up. Do you agree, Yasu?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I don't-- huh?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "...Earlier, on the fake Earth, Alicia Matel postulated to me the Earth being held on the back of a giant turtle. If the scenario on that fake Earth was planned out, the appearance of a turtle here is likely not a coincidence, but instead intended to communicate a related fact."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Do you understand now?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I guess? Like... okay, so someone said something like this before. I wasn't there, so..."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She looks at him candidly.* "But you know what was said, correct?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "You said it was about the Earth being on the back of a turtle. It sounds like a folklore thing."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Correct. It is a religious belief."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "...Uh, or maybe the giant turtle is intended to represent how small I am in comparison to it, since the fake Earth's scenario was meant as an attack on me?"

messages.content: "I have no idea. The last thing I remember here was me talking to Inspector Kamala Kyros in handcuffs."

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Well, gee, Einstein, ya think maybe you got arrested?" Laughing Man speaks up again.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "That is a nonsensical proposition. If I 'got you arrested a long while ago', why would you be here in a *jail* cell? Shouldn't you be rotting away in prison, as you deserve?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Pff. That's ancient history. I served my time. Wasn't that big of an offense." Staring Man. "This here's a different issue. Still haven't been tried yet."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "No sinner can serve enough time to learn the lesson they should. They certainly fail to, without showing repentance. Unfortunately, society fails to recognise that."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She scoffs angrily.* "What are you here for now, then?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content:
"Fascism...?" He shakes his head. "Anyway, it's a smuggling thing. Boring details. Not as interesting as whatever caused someone like you to end up here."

Laughing Man stops cracking up at your not very funny comment and seems to think of something.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Assuming I was arrested, I am also here for a 'smuggling thing'."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I am not a sinner, of course. I was framed."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Framed, huh...?" Laughing man smiles. "You know, I'm familiar with a very good lawyer."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Oh? Would that be one Gats Beagle?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content:
"No, but I'm surprised you know an Arctican. I guess you're one of those guys."

Staring man has lost track of the conversation, making a live SM reaction face.

"Hirer Dreng. Best damn lawyer around. Works miracles with the case. All for reasonable prices."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Have you... talked to him... recently?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "You could say that, yeah!"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Under the circumstances, I must doubt that he would be willing to provide me services."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She knows this is nonsense, obviously. A lawyer wouldn't care if you tried to kill him before if you could pay him enough.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I must also apply the same doubt to you, however. Hirer Dreng was running from the scene of a crime as of the last time I saw him."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Can't actually see you very well from this angle, 'detective'. I guess you can't really see me either. But you spoke enough that I remember your voice. He's me. I'm Hirer Dreng. I think we could both benefit one another, if you're willing to cooperate."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "...Ah. That..."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Make your offer. Do you want my services as a detective?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "In a manner of speaking. Though there's nothing I really want you to 'find out', exactly."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "So... do you want me to... conceal the truth?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Hey, there's nothing you'd be covering up. I'm not asking you to destroy evidence or anything. Just vouch for me. You've got some reputation here, and I've got rhetorical skills. Whatever nonsense got us in here, we can clear it up."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Do you not know why you were arrested?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Some vague details, y'know. Weird accusations about scamming. They weren't exactly forthcoming with what they were charging me with."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She chuckles.* "Is it that you pretended to come from this planet?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: He stares at you. "Well, yeah, I acted like I was from around here. But I don't think they'd be able to know that wasn't true. And, uh... surely that can't be a crime, right?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Lying is not *necessarily* a crime. Lying in court, however, is."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "You may have skill in 'rhetoric', but retaining your services as a lawyer here would be a questionable decision while you know nothing of the laws of our land. One would hope that you would know better."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: He laughs. "Around half of the job is confidence, buddy. But you're right that someone at 50% isn't the best of all options. Do you think you're gonna get a better shot, though?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Around half of *your* job is confidence. You have no idea what the job here entails."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Do you have any idea how many days there are until your trial?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Two. I think."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "And how do you intend to pass the time until then?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Probably bluff about demanding my rights so I can figure out how the law works here. Unless you've got something better."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "You could try breaking out...?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I don't do that kind of thing. More of a trickster."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *Admirable.* "How about hiring a lawyer?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: “Pff. With what?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Confidence?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: “That’s *definitely* scamming. Not sure I’m willing to take that risk.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I could pay the bill for you. How does that sound as a counter-offer?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: “Why would you do that?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I would avoid the obligation of serving something other than the truth through my testimony."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: “Obligation? I thought you were trying to refuse my offer.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I never tried to refuse anything."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Think carefully and guess again."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content:
“…Smartass. Sure. I accept.”

The other guy mutters. “Don’t know why you all are even bothering. Nobody ever gets declared not guilty.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "What are you hoping for, then?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: “A light sentence? A well equipped prison? I dunno.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Hah."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I will not let myself be imprisoned. I have things to live for."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: ((Ace Attorney))

author.name: zzazz
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\00e5cb55aacbe3824e8b8a9d53aac811-1CCD0.png

messages.content:
“That’s not your choice to make, obviously.”

Kamala enters. ((end session))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: ((session next week))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Good morning, Fainda." Kamala says this insincerely.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Hello, Inspector Kyros."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Are you feeling particularly satisfied?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Not exactly. I was able to have you transferred here, but that's one step forward for many more steps back." She eyes you suspiciously. "Do you have any awareness of what's happening around you when you're comatose?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Generally not. As the comatose individual is unconscious and mentally impaired, they are unable to process any physical signals around them."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content:
"You're certainly not bound by any of those regular rules." She pulls out a pamphlet. 
"They're calling it... Chronic Homeostatic Narcolepsy, or something. Medical anomaly. Only a handful of other potential cases, all recorded quite recently." 
She shakes her head. "I have a difficult time believing you'd be dispatched by a force so inexplicable and banal."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "How unusual." *She put a finger to her head as if thinking.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Were none of those other cases able to explain their condition?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I looked into it a little, but there was nothing I could confirm. Part of it was the language barrier. But it also seems unusual how little information is recorded. Though the first case was apparently quite some time ago, all the information I can find was published within the last month. It's as if something, or someone, was attempting to cover this subject up. Would you know anything about that...?" She stows the papers away. "At any rate..."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Do I know something about it? I may have an idea, but I am not exactly at liberty to investigate such an issue."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Tch. You're not in a position to bargain. Not like that." She tosses a folded up piece of paper through the bars. "What do you know about this thing?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She picks up the paper and examines it.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: It seems pretty clear for one that it's a photocopy of another document. It contains a lengthy series of symbols that Rikarasu does not recognize.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "It could be some type of magical rune or code?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She answers honestly.* "I have never seen this before."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content:
"Magical?" She snorts. 
"In any case. I suppose I don't have reason to assume you do know. This could be completely irrelevant." Kamala looks at the other people in earshot suspiciously, before convincing herself it doesn't matter.
"Alicia Matel is dead."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "What?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She seems slightly surprised.* "So... she left that paper as her last message? And then she was killed?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Did you kill her?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Of course not. You're only right about one thing. That this is presumably from her. Only thing in her pockets. But there's no evidence she was murdered. It was an overdose." She scoffs at the last part.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She just stands there for a moment.* "How are you so sure? If you recall, she was squatting in my house, so she would have had nowhere else to return to. And as you just said, she only had that paper in her pockets. So where could she have obtained any drug to overdose on?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "She could have easily been poisoned."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Investigation on her supplier is ongoing. Or, supply location, at least." Kamala narrows her eyes. "Why do you think she would've been poisoned, hm? Pretty unremarkable lady from outside appearances."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "You may have seen it fit to execute her yourself for her act of squatting."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "That is in no sense the punishment for that crime. Not that I'd expect you to know." She smirks. "Deflect however you want. That was a pretty bad slip-up."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She scoffs.* "What are you suggesting, exactly? That I would have conspired towards the poisoning of the person who had been assisting me before your intrusion?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Of course not. You'd have no reason or means of killing your partner."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "The only enemy I knew her to have was you. Haruka Tanaka could have also decided to poison Alicia Matel, since she had witnessed Haruka's crimes, but I find that unlikely."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "The lady you used to work for?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Precisely. And the mastermind behind the cocaine-smuggling operation."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Not that you would believe me."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I wouldn't believe you. The operation ended the moment your movements became restricted."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Have you found anything within my house? Any traces of illicit substances?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: “Yes. Though not in a quantity able to pin you as a distributor. Whatever warehouse or remote location you used… we haven’t found it.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I wish you luck with that."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Do you actually have any meaningful evidence against me?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "That should be obvious. Enough that I know the truth, and enough to hold you, but not enough that I can prove anything."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "And do you truly believe that I, of all people, would resort to illegally smuggling drugs and carefully hiding the evidence?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Yes. Is that a real question?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Yes?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Whatever. ...One last thing. Did you tell Alicia anything about your condition? The bouts of unconsciousness?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I..." *She thinks back.* "I believe I mentioned it, in a sense, yes. "Intuition Overdrive" should be able to recall the interaction."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Ah. How could I forget. Yes, that man is MIA. My most embarrassing failure. But he has to turn up eventually. Alive or dead."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Ah. So you intend to kill him too."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "It shows a lot that this country allows crazed vigilantes to become officers of the law and hide behind fake titles."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I never killed anyone. Why would I ever do that for a crime such as resisting arrest? He's not some serial killer. You're pretty clearly trying to get my goat with absurd personal attacks. I'll find some other person to deal with you. Have a nice day."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "'*That would be absurd.*' Truly the most impenetrable of defenses."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Did you not spend months chasing after me, a perfectly innocent woman, on your own agenda entirely by yourself? And you expect me to believe a murder or two is out of the question?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "You may have gaslit yourself into forgetting your own crimes. It would not do well for the mental state of a 'criminal investigator' to have committed and concealed a murder. But the likelihood remains nonetheless."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "You're so fucking bad at this." She leaves.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She mumbles to herself.* "Without love, it cannot be 'seen'.'

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She chuckles, then yells out to the bars.* "Did you hear all of that, Hirer Dreng?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Most of it!"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

author.name: pichuis
